## PAGE 1 — index.html (Cashier)

Layout: two columns
- Left (65%): product grid
- Right (35%): cart sidebar

### Product Grid
- Fetch all products from GET /api/products
- Render each as a card: product name (bold), price (accent color), "إضافة" button
- CSS Grid: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(150px, 1fr))

### Cart Sidebar
- List of added items: name, quantity controls (+ / −), line total
- Remove button per item (×)
- Total at bottom (large, bold)
- "تأكيد الطلب" button (full width, accent color)
- On confirm: POST /api/orders → show receipt modal

### Receipt Modal
- Overlay (rgba black background)
- White centered card
- Order number, date & time
- Items list with quantities and prices
- Grand total
- QR code (generated from order JSON using qrcode.js, displayed as canvas)
- "طباعة" button → window.print()
- "إغلاق" button
- Print styles: hide sidebar and modal chrome, show receipt content only

---

## PAGE 2 — products.html (Product Management)

### Top bar
- Page title "إدارة المنتجات"
- "إضافة منتج" button (opens add form)

### Add/Edit Form (toggle visible, hidden by default)
- Input: اسم المنتج (required)
- Input: السعر (number, required)
- Input: الفئة (text, e.g. برجر / مشروب / إضافات)
- "حفظ" button → POST or PUT /api/products
- "إلغاء" button → hide form

### Products Table
- Columns: الاسم | الفئة | السعر | إجراءات
- Actions: "تعديل" (fills form with data) | "حذف" (DELETE with confirm dialog)
- Fetch on page load from GET /api/products
- Re-render table after every add/edit/delete

---

## PAGE 3 — dashboard.html (Statistics)

### Summary Cards Row (4 cards)
- إجمالي طلبات اليوم
- إيرادات اليوم (بالجنيه)
- إجمالي الطلبات الكلي
- إجمالي الإيرادات الكلي
- Fetch from GET /api/orders/stats

### Chart
- Bar chart using Chart.js
- X axis: last 7 days (formatted as day/month)
- Y axis: number of orders
- Accent color bars (#FF6B35)
- Fetch daily data from GET /api/orders/stats

### Recent Orders Table
- Columns: رقم الطلب | عدد الأصناف | الإجمالي | التاريخ والوقت
- Last 20 orders, newest first
- Fetch from GET /api/orders?limit=20

---

## BACKEND — server.js

```js
require('dotenv').config()
const express = require('express')
const mongoose = require('mongoose')
const cors = require('cors')

const app = express()
app.use(cors())
app.use(express.json())
app.use(express.static('frontend'))  // serve HTML files directly

app.use('/api/products', require('./routes/products'))
app.use('/api/orders', require('./routes/orders'))

mongoose.connect(process.env.MONGO_URI)
  .then(() => app.listen(process.env.PORT || 5000,
    () => console.log('Server running')))
```

---

## MONGODB SCHEMAS

### Product (models/Product.js)
```js
{
  name:      { type: String, required: true },
  price:     { type: Number, required: true },
  category:  { type: String, default: 'عام' },
  createdAt: { type: Date,   default: Date.now }
}
```

### Order (models/Order.js)
```js
{
  orderNumber: { type: Number },   // auto-increment on save
  items: [{
    productId: { type: mongoose.Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'Product' },
    name:      String,
    price:     Number,
    quantity:  Number
  }],
  total:     { type: Number, required: true },
  createdAt: { type: Date, default: Date.now }
}
```

Auto-increment orderNumber using pre-save hook:
find the max orderNumber in collection and add 1.

---

## API ENDPOINTS

### Products
| Method | Endpoint            | Action         |
|--------|---------------------|----------------|
| GET    | /api/products       | get all        |
| POST   | /api/products       | create         |
| PUT    | /api/products/:id   | update         |
| DELETE | /api/products/:id   | delete         |

### Orders
| Method | Endpoint            | Action                          |
|--------|---------------------|---------------------------------|
| GET    | /api/orders         | list all (supports ?limit=N)    |
| POST   | /api/orders         | create new order                |
| GET    | /api/orders/stats   | aggregated stats + daily counts |

### /api/orders/stats response shape
```json
{
  "todayCount": 12,
  "todayRevenue": 840,
  "totalCount": 320,
  "totalRevenue": 21500,
  "daily": [
    { "date": "2024-01-10", "count": 8,  "revenue": 560 },
    { "date": "2024-01-11", "count": 12, "revenue": 840 }
  ]
}
```

---

## api.js (frontend — all fetch calls here)

```js
const BASE = 'http://localhost:5000/api'

export const getProducts   = () => fetch(`${BASE}/products`).then(r => r.json())
export const createProduct = (data) => fetch(`${BASE}/products`, { method:'POST', headers:{'Content-Type':'application/json'}, body: JSON.stringify(data) }).then(r => r.json())
export const updateProduct = (id, data) => fetch(`${BASE}/products/${id}`, { method:'PUT', headers:{'Content-Type':'application/json'}, body: JSON.stringify(data) }).then(r => r.json())
export const deleteProduct = (id) => fetch(`${BASE}/products/${id}`, { method:'DELETE' }).then(r => r.json())

export const createOrder   = (data) => fetch(`${BASE}/orders`, { method:'POST', headers:{'Content-Type':'application/json'}, body: JSON.stringify(data) }).then(r => r.json())
export const getOrders     = (limit=20) => fetch(`${BASE}/orders?limit=${limit}`).then(r => r.json())
export const getStats      = () => fetch(`${BASE}/orders/stats`).then(r => r.json())
```

