## README.md — include setup steps:
1. cd backend && npm install
2. create .env file
3. node server.js
4. open browser at http://localhost:5000

---

## BUILD ORDER (follow this sequence strictly)

1. backend: server.js + .env + npm init
2. backend: models (Product, Order)
3. backend: controllers (products, orders with stats aggregation)
4. backend: routes
5. frontend: style.css (full design system)
6. frontend: api.js
7. frontend: index.html + cashier.js (product grid, cart, receipt modal, QR)
8. frontend: products.html + products.js (table, form, CRUD)
9. frontend: dashboard.html + dashboard.js (cards, chart, recent orders)

Build each step fully before moving to the next.
Do not skip steps or combine them.
After each file is complete, confirm it works before continuing.
